subject: p14851532
History: Chest pain, shortness of breath in a patient with history of non-small cell lung cancer.
Findings: PA and lateral views of the chest were reviewed. The cardiomediastinal and hilar contours are unremarkable. RCA stent is noted. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. Flattened hemidiaphragms with widened AP diameter are consistent with emphysematous changes. Extensive parenchymal opacities with distortion in both apices and chain sutures in the right upper lobe are reflective of known malignancy and post treatment changes. There is no focal consolidation concerning for pneumonia. There is no pulmonary edema.
Impression: No acute process in a patient with known non-small cell lung cancer with extensive post treatment changes and emphysema.
